sentences: This issue was taken up in SBI plenary on 6 November.
Discussions focused on the Secretariat's report on national greenhouse gas inventory data from Annex I parties (FCCC/SBI/2006/26).
The G-77/China expressed concern at rising Annex I greenhouse gas emissions and delays in reporting, urging full implementation of Protocol commitments.
The EU expressed confidence that it will meet its Kyoto targets.
Australia contested the report's presentation of national greenhouse gas inventory data, especially exclusion of LULUCF data.
The SBI noted the report in plenary.
